SSRS >> SQL server Report services. These are used to generate the reports.
Reports can be:
1.Printed
2.Exported to PDF
3.Exported to Excel
4.Sent via email
5.Displayed in the browser. For example the reports can be as 
                                            Sales Invoice
                                            Purchase Order
                                            Customer Statement
                                            Vendor Payment Report
                                            Trial Balance

SSRS reports contains the following components 
 >> Table / Query >> Data Provider >> DataSets >> Report Design >> Controller class 

There are three types of SSRS reports in D365 
1.Query Based Report 
    >> Uses AOT Query as data source.
    >> Table >> Query >> Dataset >> Report Design
    >> These are used for Simple Reports and List Reports


2.RDP Report (Report Data Provider)
    >> Used when business logic is needed.
    >> Table >> Class >> temp Table >> Data set >> Report Design
    >> These are used for Multiple Tables , Complex caluclations etc

3.DP with Contract Report(Most Commonly Used )
    >>  Uses Data Contract + RDP + Controller.
    >> Data Contract (Parameters) >> controller class >> RDP class >> temp Table >> DataSet >>  report Design
    >> these are used mainly in parameter reports.


